AN ACT relating to public works; providing a declaration of legislative intent
regarding the payment of prevailing wages to workers employed by a
contractor or subcontractor to perform construction work on certain
projects awarded by a public utility ; [relating to infrastructure for
natural gas;] requiring , with certain exceptions, that a contractor or
subcontractor who is awarded a contract for construction work on
certain [infrastructure] projects by a public utility to comply with
prevailing wage provisions applicable to public works, even if the
construction work does not qualify as a public work; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law sets forth general provisions applicable to public works, including
2 provisions requiring, with certain exceptions, the payment of prevailing wages for public
3 works projects. (NRS 338.013-338.090) Section 2 of this bill makes [a declaration] certain
4 declarations of legislative intent [finding that] relating to the payment of prevailing wages to
5 workers employed by a contractor or subcontractor to perform construction work on [projects]
6 a significant operational or capital requirement project awarded by a public utility .
7 [relating to infrastructure for natural gas is necessary for the safety of the public and to ensure
8 the highest quality of work on such projects.] Section 3 of this bill requires , with certain
9 exceptions, that a contractor or subcontractor who is awarded a contract for construction
10 work on a significant [natural gas infrastructure] operational or capital requirement project
11 by a public utility to comply with prevailing wage provisions applicable to public works, even
12 if the construction work does not qualify as a public work. Section 3 also defines “public
13 utility” and “significant [natural gas infrastructure] operational or capital requirement
14 project” for the purposes of that section.

