THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 338 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto the
2 provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. The Legislature hereby finds and declares that the payment of
4 prevailing wages to workers employed by a contractor or subcontractor to
5 perform construction work on [projects] a significant operational or capital
6 requirement project awarded by a public utility [relating to infrastructure for
7 natural gas is necessary for the safety of the public and to ensure] is essential to:
8 1. Increasing the number of skilled construction workers in this State;
9 2. Ensuring the highest quality of work on such projects [.] ;
10 3. Ensuring the safe and timely completion of such projects; and
11 4. Ensuring that the residents of this State have access to safe, reliable and
12 affordable energy resources.
13 Sec. 3. 1. [The] Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, the
14 provisions of NRS 338.013 to 338.090, inclusive, apply to any contract for
15 construction work awarded by a public utility to a contractor or subcontractor on
16 a significant operational or capital requirement [natural gas infrastructure]
17 project, even if the construction work does not qualify as a public work, as
18 defined in NRS 338.010.
19 2. The provisions of subsection 1 do not apply to any contract where the
20 primary construction work is performed pursuant to a collective bargaining
21 agreement or project labor agreement with a public utility.
22 3. As used in this section:
23 (a) “Public utility” [has the meaning ascribed to it in] means a utility that
24 purchases natural gas for retail and an electric utility as defined in NRS [704.020
25 and 704.021.] 704.7571.
26 (b) “Significant [natural gas infrastructure] operational or capital
27 requirement project” means:
28 (1) The construction or replacement of a [new facility for the
29 transmission, distribution, compression or storage of] natural gas [;] pipeline
30 approved in a plan submitted pursuant to NRS 704.991; or
31 (2) The [rehabilitation, replacement, modification, upgrade, uprate or
32 update of an existing] construction of a new generation electric utility facility [for
33 the transmission, distribution, compression or storage of natural gas; or] of not
34 less than 50 megawatts and that is approved in a plan submitted pursuant to NRS
35 704.741.
36 [(3) Any series of projects listed in subparagraphs (1) and (2) for which
37 the anticipated cost of the series of projects exceeds the cost threshold established
38 by the Public Utilities Commission of Nevada pursuant to subsection 3 of NRS
39 704.991.]
40 Sec. 4. The provisions of section 3 of this act do not apply to any contract
41 entered into before October 1, 2025.

